UPEC (Unique Progrm Execution Checking) is a formal approach for detecting vulnerabilities to transient execution attacks in out-of-order processors developed by the Electronic Design Automation Group (https://www.eit.uni-kl.de/eis/research/) at TU Kaiserslautern, Germany.

UPEC paper: https://arxiv.org/abs/1812.04975
UPEC with Extension for Out-of-Order Processors: https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/9218572
